87 // Although this default value is arbitrary, it is not random. It is assumed ----
88 // that a condition that evaluates the same way by a higher percentage than ----
89 // this is best represented as control flow. Therefore, the default value N ----
90 // should be set such that the win from N% correct executions is greater than ----
91 // the loss from (100 - N)% mispredicted executions for the majority of ----
92 // intended targets. ----
93 BranchProbability getPredictableBranchThreshold() const { 0
94 return BranchProbability(99, 100); 0

257 bool isLegalNTStore(Type *DataType, Align Alignment) const { 0
258 // By default, assume nontemporal memory stores are available for stores ----
259 // that are aligned and have a size that is a power of 2. ----
260 unsigned DataSize = DL.getTypeStoreSize(DataType); 0
261 return Alignment >= DataSize && isPowerOf2_32(DataSize); 0
262 } ----

266 // are aligned and have a size that is a power of 2. ----
267 unsigned DataSize = DL.getTypeStoreSize(DataType); 0
268 return Alignment >= DataSize && isPowerOf2_32(DataSize); 0

505 InstructionCost getArithmeticInstrCost( 0
506 unsigned Opcode, Type *Ty, TTI::TargetCostKind CostKind, ----
507 TTI::OperandValueInfo Opd1Info, TTI::OperandValueInfo Opd2Info, ----
508 ArrayRef Args, ----
509 const Instruction *CxtI = nullptr) const { ----
510 // Widenable conditions will eventually lower into constants, so some ----
511 // operations with them will be trivially optimized away. ----
512 auto IsWidenableCondition = [](const Value *V) { 0
513 if (auto *II = dyn_cast(V)) 0
514 if (II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::experimental_widenable_condition) 0
515 return true; 0
516 return false; 0
517 }; ----
518 // FIXME: A number of transformation tests seem to require these values ----
519 // which seems a little odd for how arbitary there are. ----
520 switch (Opcode) { 0
521 default: 0
522 break; 0
523 case Instruction::FDiv: 0
524 case Instruction::FRem: ----
525 case Instruction::SDiv: ----
526 case Instruction::SRem: ----
527 case Instruction::UDiv: ----
528 case Instruction::URem: ----
529 // FIXME: Unlikely to be true for CodeSize. ----
530 return TTI::TCC_Expensive; 0
531 case Instruction::And: 0
532 case Instruction::Or: ----
533 if (any_of(Args, IsWidenableCondition)) 0
534 return TTI::TCC_Free; 0
535 break; 0
536 } ----
537 ----
538 // Assume a 3cy latency for fp arithmetic ops. ----
539 if (CostKind == TTI::TCK_Latency) 0
540 if (Ty->getScalarType()->isFloatingPointTy()) 0
541 return 3; 0
542 ----
543 return 1; 0
544 } ----

553 InstructionCost getCastInstrCost(unsigned Opcode, Type *Dst, Type *Src, 0
554 TTI::CastContextHint CCH, ----
555 TTI::TargetCostKind CostKind, ----
556 const Instruction *I) const { ----
557 switch (Opcode) { 0
558 default: 0
559 break; 0
560 case Instruction::IntToPtr: { 0
561 unsigned SrcSize = Src->getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
562 if (DL.isLegalInteger(SrcSize) && 0
563 SrcSize <= DL.getPointerTypeSizeInBits(Dst)) 0
564 return 0; 0
565 break; 0
566 } ----
567 case Instruction::PtrToInt: { 0
568 unsigned DstSize = Dst->getScalarSizeInBits(); 0
569 if (DL.isLegalInteger(DstSize) && 0
570 DstSize >= DL.getPointerTypeSizeInBits(Src)) 0
571 return 0; 0
572 break; 0
573 } ----
574 case Instruction::BitCast: 0
575 if (Dst == Src || (Dst->isPointerTy() && Src->isPointerTy())) 0
576 // Identity and pointer-to-pointer casts are free. ----
577 return 0; 0
578 break; 0
579 case Instruction::Trunc: { 0
580 // trunc to a native type is free (assuming the target has compare and ----
581 // shift-right of the same width). ----
582 TypeSize DstSize = DL.getTypeSizeInBits(Dst); 0
583 if (!DstSize.isScalable() && DL.isLegalInteger(DstSize.getFixedValue())) 0
584 return 0; 0
585 break; 0
586 } ----
587 } ----
588 return 1; 0
589 } ----

894 protected: ----
895 // Obtain the minimum required size to hold the value (without the sign) ----
896 // In case of a vector it returns the min required size for one element. ----
897 unsigned minRequiredElementSize(const Value *Val, bool &isSigned) const { ----
898 if (isa(Val) || isa(Val)) { ----
899 const auto *VectorValue = cast(Val); ----
900 ----
901 // In case of a vector need to pick the max between the min ----
902 // required size for each element ----
903 auto *VT = cast(Val->getType()); ----
904 ----
905 // Assume unsigned elements ----
906 isSigned = false; ----
907 ----
908 // The max required size is the size of the vector element type ----
909 unsigned MaxRequiredSize = ----
910 VT->getElementType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits().getFixedValue(); ----
911 ----
912 unsigned MinRequiredSize = 0; ----
913 for (unsigned i = 0, e = VT->getNumElements(); i < e; ++i) { ----
914 if (auto *IntElement = ----
915 dyn_cast(VectorValue->getAggregateElement(i))) { ----
916 bool signedElement = IntElement->getValue().isNegative(); ----
917 // Get the element min required size. ----
918 unsigned ElementMinRequiredSize = ----
919 IntElement->getValue().getSignificantBits() - 1; ----
920 // In case one element is signed then all the vector is signed. ----
921 isSigned |= signedElement; ----
922 // Save the max required bit size between all the elements. ----
923 MinRequiredSize = std::max(MinRequiredSize, ElementMinRequiredSize); ----
924 } else { ----
925 // not an int constant element ----
926 return MaxRequiredSize; ----
927 } ----
928 } ----
929 return MinRequiredSize; ----
930 } ----
931 ----
932 if (const auto *CI = dyn_cast(Val)) { ----
933 isSigned = CI->getValue().isNegative(); ----
934 return CI->getValue().getSignificantBits() - 1; ----
935 } ----
936 ----
937 if (const auto *Cast = dyn_cast(Val)) { ----
938 isSigned = true; ----
939 return Cast->getSrcTy()->getScalarSizeInBits() - 1; ----
940 } ----
941 ----
942 if (const auto *Cast = dyn_cast(Val)) { ----
943 isSigned = false; ----
944 return Cast->getSrcTy()->getScalarSizeInBits(); ----
945 } ----
946 ----
947 isSigned = false; ----
948 return Val->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits(); ----
949 } ----
950 ----
951 bool isStridedAccess(const SCEV *Ptr) const { ----
952 return Ptr && isa(Ptr); ----
953 } ----
954 ----
955 const SCEVConstant *getConstantStrideStep(ScalarEvolution *SE, ----
956 const SCEV *Ptr) const { ----
957 if (!isStridedAccess(Ptr)) ----
958 return nullptr; ----
959 const SCEVAddRecExpr *AddRec = cast(Ptr); ----
960 return dyn_cast(AddRec->getStepRecurrence(*SE)); ----
961 } ----
962 ----
963 bool isConstantStridedAccessLessThan(ScalarEvolution *SE, const SCEV *Ptr, ----
964 int64_t MergeDistance) const { ----
965 const SCEVConstant *Step = getConstantStrideStep(SE, Ptr); ----
966 if (!Step) ----
967 return false; ----
968 APInt StrideVal = Step->getAPInt(); ----
969 if (StrideVal.getBitWidth() > 64) ----
970 return false; ----
971 // FIXME: Need to take absolute value for negative stride case. ----
972 return StrideVal.getSExtValue() < MergeDistance; ----
973 } ----
974 }; ----
975 ----
976 /// CRTP base class for use as a mix-in that aids implementing ----
977 /// a TargetTransformInfo-compatible class. ----
978 template ----
979 class TargetTransformInfoImplCRTPBase : public TargetTransformInfoImplBase { ----
980 private: ----
981 typedef TargetTransformInfoImplBase BaseT; ----
982 ----
983 protected: ----
984 explicit TargetTransformInfoImplCRTPBase(const DataLayout &DL) : BaseT(DL) {} 18 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
985 ----
986 public: ----
987 using BaseT::getGEPCost; ----
988 ----
989 InstructionCost getGEPCost(Type *PointeeType, const Value *Ptr, 0
990 ArrayRef Operands, Type *AccessType, ----
991 TTI::TargetCostKind CostKind) { ----
992 assert(PointeeType && Ptr && "can't get GEPCost of nullptr"); 0
993 auto *BaseGV = dyn_cast(Ptr->stripPointerCasts()); 0
994 bool HasBaseReg = (BaseGV == nullptr); 0
995 ----
996 auto PtrSizeBits = DL.getPointerTypeSizeInBits(Ptr->getType()); 0
997 APInt BaseOffset(PtrSizeBits, 0); 0
998 int64_t Scale = 0; 0
999 ----
1000 auto GTI = gep_type_begin(PointeeType, Operands); 0
1001 Type *TargetType = nullptr; 0
1002 ----
1003 // Handle the case where the GEP instruction has a single operand, ----
1004 // the basis, therefore TargetType is a nullptr. ----
1005 if (Operands.empty()) 0
1006 return !BaseGV ? TTI::TCC_Free : TTI::TCC_Basic; 0
1007 ----
1008 for (auto I = Operands.begin(); I != Operands.end(); ++I, ++GTI) { 0
1009 TargetType = GTI.getIndexedType(); 0
1010 // We assume that the cost of Scalar GEP with constant index and the ----
1011 // cost of Vector GEP with splat constant index are the same. ----
1012 const ConstantInt *ConstIdx = dyn_cast(*I); 0
1013 if (!ConstIdx) 0
1014 if (auto Splat = getSplatValue(*I)) 0
1015 ConstIdx = dyn_cast(Splat); 0
1016 if (StructType *STy = GTI.getStructTypeOrNull()) { 0
1017 // For structures the index is always splat or scalar constant ----
1018 assert(ConstIdx && "Unexpected GEP index"); 0
1019 uint64_t Field = ConstIdx->getZExtValue(); 0
1020 BaseOffset += DL.getStructLayout(STy)->getElementOffset(Field); 0
1021 } else { ----
1022 // If this operand is a scalable type, bail out early. ----
1023 // TODO: handle scalable vectors ----
1024 if (isa(TargetType)) 0
1025 return TTI::TCC_Basic; 0
1026 int64_t ElementSize = 0
1027 DL.getTypeAllocSize(GTI.getIndexedType()).getFixedValue(); 0
1028 if (ConstIdx) { 0
1029 BaseOffset += 0
1030 ConstIdx->getValue().sextOrTrunc(PtrSizeBits) * ElementSize; 0
1031 } else { ----
1032 // Needs scale register. ----
1033 if (Scale != 0) 0
1034 // No addressing mode takes two scale registers. ----
1035 return TTI::TCC_Basic; 0
1036 Scale = ElementSize; 0
1037 } ----
1038 } ----
1039 } ----
1040 ----
1041 // If we haven't been provided a hint, use the target type for now. ----
1042 // ----
1043 // TODO: Take a look at potentially removing this: This is *slightly* wrong ----
1044 // as it's possible to have a GEP with a foldable target type but a memory ----
1045 // access that isn't foldable. For example, this load isn't foldable on ----
1046 // RISC-V: ----
1047 // ----
1048 // %p = getelementptr i32, ptr %base, i32 42 ----
1049 // %x = load <2 x i32>, ptr %p ----
1050 if (!AccessType) 0
1051 AccessType = TargetType; 0
1052 ----
1053 // If the final address of the GEP is a legal addressing mode for the given ----
1054 // access type, then we can fold it into its users. ----
1055 if (static_cast(this)->isLegalAddressingMode( 0
1056 AccessType, const_cast(BaseGV), ----
1057 BaseOffset.sextOrTrunc(64).getSExtValue(), HasBaseReg, Scale, ----
1058 Ptr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace())) ----
1059 return TTI::TCC_Free; 0
1060 ----
1061 // TODO: Instead of returning TCC_Basic here, we should use ----
1062 // getArithmeticInstrCost. Or better yet, provide a hook to let the target ----
1063 // model it. ----
1064 return TTI::TCC_Basic; 0
1065 } 0
1066 ----
1067 InstructionCost getPointersChainCost(ArrayRef Ptrs, 0
1068 const Value *Base, ----
1069 const TTI::PointersChainInfo &Info, ----
1070 Type *AccessTy, ----
1071 TTI::TargetCostKind CostKind) { ----
1072 InstructionCost Cost = TTI::TCC_Free; 0
1073 // In the basic model we take into account GEP instructions only ----
1074 // (although here can come alloca instruction, a value, constants and/or ----
1075 // constant expressions, PHIs, bitcasts ... whatever allowed to be used as a ----
1076 // pointer). Typically, if Base is a not a GEP-instruction and all the ----
1077 // pointers are relative to the same base address, all the rest are ----
1078 // either GEP instructions, PHIs, bitcasts or constants. When we have same ----
1079 // base, we just calculate cost of each non-Base GEP as an ADD operation if ----
1080 // any their index is a non-const. ----
1081 // If no known dependecies between the pointers cost is calculated as a sum ----
1082 // of costs of GEP instructions. ----
1083 for (const Value *V : Ptrs) { 0
1084 const auto *GEP = dyn_cast(V); 0
1085 if (!GEP) 0
1086 continue; 0
1087 if (Info.isSameBase() && V != Base) { 0
1088 if (GEP->hasAllConstantIndices()) 0
1089 continue; 0
1090 Cost += static_cast(this)->getArithmeticInstrCost( 0
1091 Instruction::Add, GEP->getType(), CostKind, ----
1092 {TTI::OK_AnyValue, TTI::OP_None}, {TTI::OK_AnyValue, TTI::OP_None}, ----
1093 std::nullopt); ----
1094 } else { ----
1095 SmallVector Indices(GEP->indices()); 0
1096 Cost += static_cast(this)->getGEPCost(GEP->getSourceElementType(), 0
1097 GEP->getPointerOperand(), ----
1098 Indices, AccessTy, CostKind); ----
1099 } 0
1100 } ----
1101 return Cost; 0
1102 } ----
1103 ----
1104 InstructionCost getInstructionCost(const User *U, 0
1105 ArrayRef Operands, ----
1106 TTI::TargetCostKind CostKind) { ----
1107 using namespace llvm::PatternMatch; ----
1108 ----
1109 auto *TargetTTI = static_cast(this); 0
1110 // Handle non-intrinsic calls, invokes, and callbr. ----
1111 // FIXME: Unlikely to be true for anything but CodeSize. ----
1112 auto *CB = dyn_cast(U); 0
1113 if (CB && !isa(U)) { 0
1114 if (const Function *F = CB->getCalledFunction()) { 0
1115 if (!TargetTTI->isLoweredToCall(F)) 0
1116 return TTI::TCC_Basic; // Give a basic cost if it will be lowered 0
1117 ----
1118 return TTI::TCC_Basic * (F->getFunctionType()->getNumParams() + 1); 0
1119 } ----
1120 // For indirect or other calls, scale cost by number of arguments. ----
1121 return TTI::TCC_Basic * (CB->arg_size() + 1); 0
1122 } ----
1123 ----
1124 Type *Ty = U->getType(); 0
1125 unsigned Opcode = Operator::getOpcode(U); 0
1126 auto *I = dyn_cast(U); 0
1127 switch (Opcode) { 0
1128 default: 0
1129 break; 0
1130 case Instruction::Call: { 0
1131 assert(isa(U) && "Unexpected non-intrinsic call"); 0
1132 auto *Intrinsic = cast(U); 0
1133 IntrinsicCostAttributes CostAttrs(Intrinsic->getIntrinsicID(), *CB); 0
1134 return TargetTTI->getIntrinsicInstrCost(CostAttrs, CostKind); 0
1135 } 0
1136 case Instruction::Br: 0
1137 case Instruction::Ret: ----
1138 case Instruction::PHI: ----
1139 case Instruction::Switch: ----
1140 return TargetTTI->getCFInstrCost(Opcode, CostKind, I); 0
1141 case Instruction::ExtractValue: 0
1142 case Instruction::Freeze: ----
1143 return TTI::TCC_Free; 0
1144 case Instruction::Alloca: 0
1145 if (cast(U)->isStaticAlloca()) 0
1146 return TTI::TCC_Free; 0
1147 break; 0
1148 case Instruction::GetElementPtr: { 0
1149 const auto *GEP = cast(U); 0
1150 Type *AccessType = nullptr; 0
1151 // For now, only provide the AccessType in the simple case where the GEP ----
1152 // only has one user. ----
1153 if (GEP->hasOneUser() && I) 0
1154 AccessType = I->user_back()->getAccessType(); 0
1155 ----
1156 return TargetTTI->getGEPCost(GEP->getSourceElementType(), 0
1157 Operands.front(), Operands.drop_front(), 0
1158 AccessType, CostKind); 0
1159 } ----
1160 case Instruction::Add: 0
1161 case Instruction::FAdd: ----
1162 case Instruction::Sub: ----
1163 case Instruction::FSub: ----
1164 case Instruction::Mul: ----
1165 case Instruction::FMul: ----
1166 case Instruction::UDiv: ----
1167 case Instruction::SDiv: ----
1168 case Instruction::FDiv: ----
1169 case Instruction::URem: ----
1170 case Instruction::SRem: ----
1171 case Instruction::FRem: ----
1172 case Instruction::Shl: ----
1173 case Instruction::LShr: ----
1174 case Instruction::AShr: ----
1175 case Instruction::And: ----
1176 case Instruction::Or: ----
1177 case Instruction::Xor: ----
1178 case Instruction::FNeg: { ----
1179 const TTI::OperandValueInfo Op1Info = TTI::getOperandInfo(Operands[0]); 0
1180 TTI::OperandValueInfo Op2Info; 0
1181 if (Opcode != Instruction::FNeg) 0
1182 Op2Info = TTI::getOperandInfo(Operands[1]); 0
1183 return TargetTTI->getArithmeticInstrCost(Opcode, Ty, CostKind, Op1Info, 0
1184 Op2Info, Operands, I); 0
1185 } ----
1186 case Instruction::IntToPtr: 0
1187 case Instruction::PtrToInt: ----
1188 case Instruction::SIToFP: ----
1189 case Instruction::UIToFP: ----
1190 case Instruction::FPToUI: ----
1191 case Instruction::FPToSI: ----
1192 case Instruction::Trunc: ----
1193 case Instruction::FPTrunc: ----
1194 case Instruction::BitCast: ----
1195 case Instruction::FPExt: ----
1196 case Instruction::SExt: ----
1197 case Instruction::ZExt: ----
1198 case Instruction::AddrSpaceCast: { ----
1199 Type *OpTy = Operands[0]->getType(); 0
1200 return TargetTTI->getCastInstrCost( 0
1201 Opcode, Ty, OpTy, TTI::getCastContextHint(I), CostKind, I); 0
1202 } ----
1203 case Instruction::Store: { 0
1204 auto *SI = cast(U); 0
1205 Type *ValTy = Operands[0]->getType(); 0
1206 TTI::OperandValueInfo OpInfo = TTI::getOperandInfo(Operands[0]); 0
1207 return TargetTTI->getMemoryOpCost(Opcode, ValTy, SI->getAlign(), 0
1208 SI->getPointerAddressSpace(), CostKind, ----
1209 OpInfo, I); 0
1210 } ----
1211 case Instruction::Load: { 0
1212 // FIXME: Arbitary cost which could come from the backend. ----
1213 if (CostKind == TTI::TCK_Latency) 0
1214 return 4; 0
1215 auto *LI = cast(U); 0
1216 Type *LoadType = U->getType(); 0
1217 // If there is a non-register sized type, the cost estimation may expand ----
1218 // it to be several instructions to load into multiple registers on the ----
1219 // target. But, if the only use of the load is a trunc instruction to a ----
1220 // register sized type, the instruction selector can combine these ----
1221 // instructions to be a single load. So, in this case, we use the ----
1222 // destination type of the trunc instruction rather than the load to ----
1223 // accurately estimate the cost of this load instruction. ----
1224 if (CostKind == TTI::TCK_CodeSize && LI->hasOneUse() && 0
1225 !LoadType->isVectorTy()) { 0
1226 if (const TruncInst *TI = dyn_cast(*LI->user_begin())) 0
1227 LoadType = TI->getDestTy(); 0
1228 } ----
1229 return TargetTTI->getMemoryOpCost(Opcode, LoadType, LI->getAlign(), 0
1230 LI->getPointerAddressSpace(), CostKind, ----
1231 {TTI::OK_AnyValue, TTI::OP_None}, I); 0
1232 } ----
1233 case Instruction::Select: { 0
1234 const Value *Op0, *Op1; ----
1235 if (match(U, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(Op0), m_Value(Op1))) || 0
1236 match(U, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(Op0), m_Value(Op1)))) { 0
1237 // select x, y, false --> x & y ----
1238 // select x, true, y --> x | y ----
1239 const auto Op1Info = TTI::getOperandInfo(Op0); 0
1240 const auto Op2Info = TTI::getOperandInfo(Op1); 0
1241 assert(Op0->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits() == 1 && 0
1242 Op1->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits() == 1); ----
1243 ----
1244 SmallVector Operands{Op0, Op1}; 0
1245 return TargetTTI->getArithmeticInstrCost( 0
1246 match(U, m_LogicalOr()) ? Instruction::Or : Instruction::And, Ty, 0
1247 CostKind, Op1Info, Op2Info, Operands, I); 0
1248 } 0
1249 Type *CondTy = Operands[0]->getType(); 0
1250 return TargetTTI->getCmpSelInstrCost(Opcode, U->getType(), CondTy, 0
1251 CmpInst::BAD_ICMP_PREDICATE, ----
1252 CostKind, I); 0
1253 } ----
1254 case Instruction::ICmp: 0
1255 case Instruction::FCmp: { ----
1256 Type *ValTy = Operands[0]->getType(); 0
1257 // TODO: Also handle ICmp/FCmp constant expressions. ----
1258 return TargetTTI->getCmpSelInstrCost(Opcode, ValTy, U->getType(), 0
1259 I ? cast(I)->getPredicate() 0
1260 : CmpInst::BAD_ICMP_PREDICATE, ----
1261 CostKind, I); 0
1262 } ----
1263 case Instruction::InsertElement: { 0
1264 auto *IE = dyn_cast(U); 0
1265 if (!IE) 0
1266 return TTI::TCC_Basic; // FIXME 0
1267 unsigned Idx = -1; 0
1268 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast(Operands[2])) 0
1269 if (CI->getValue().getActiveBits() <= 32) 0
1270 Idx = CI->getZExtValue(); 0
1271 return TargetTTI->getVectorInstrCost(*IE, Ty, CostKind, Idx); 0
1272 } ----
1273 case Instruction::ShuffleVector: { 0
1274 auto *Shuffle = dyn_cast(U); 0
1275 if (!Shuffle) 0
1276 return TTI::TCC_Basic; // FIXME 0
1277 ----
1278 auto *VecTy = cast(U->getType()); 0
1279 auto *VecSrcTy = cast(Operands[0]->getType()); 0
1280 int NumSubElts, SubIndex; ----
1281 ----
1282 if (Shuffle->changesLength()) { 0
1283 // Treat a 'subvector widening' as a free shuffle. ----
1284 if (Shuffle->increasesLength() && Shuffle->isIdentityWithPadding()) 0
